text: Stor-Elvdal is a municipality in Innlandet county, Norway. 2,318 people lived there (as of 2022). The inhabitants had the hightest rate of broken marriages (in the country, as of 2023), for those that are between 66 and 16-years old.https://www.nettavisen.no/okonomi/her-er-det-flest-som-skiller-seg-ikke- morsomt/s/5-95-1711164.
